{
  "texts": [
    "PS1-10afx was first reported by Chornock et al. (2013) as an unusual superluminous SN.",
    "However, shortly thereafter, Quimby et al. (2013) showed that it was a perfect match to a lensed SN Ia at redshift z = 1.388, with a large amplification, μ ∼ 30.",
    "Quimby et al. (2014) eventually also identified a foreground lens, at z = 1.117.",
    "Even if the putative lensing object was too close to the SN, it was consistent with lensing models and existing data.",
    "Since the lensed SN Ia classification only gained acceptance four years after the explosion, further investigation of the lensing nature of the SN or its type was not possible."
  ]
}